  "prompt": "What are the best documentary websites?",
  "response": "There are several excellent websites where you can find a wide range of documentaries on various subjects. Here are some of the best ones:\n\n1. **Netflix** - A popular streaming platform with a large selection of acclaimed documentaries ranging from nature and science to social issues and true crime.\n\n2. **Amazon Prime Video** - Offers a variety of documentaries as part of its subscription service or for rental/purchase.\n\n3. **YouTube** - A vast repository of documentaries, including user-uploaded content as well as professionally produced films. Channels like National Geographic, PBS, and others host high-quality documentaries.\n\n4. **Documentary Heaven** - A website dedicated to curating a variety of free documentaries across multiple genres and topics.\n\n5. **DocuWiki** - A comprehensive platform that provides links to free documentaries available online, categorized by subject.\n\n6. **Kanopy** - A streaming service that provides access to a wide range of documentaries and educational films, available for free through participating libraries and universities.\n\n7. **PBS** - The Public Broadcasting Service offers a variety of documentaries via its website, including many award-winning series.\n\n8. **Vimeo** - Some independent filmmakers upload their documentaries to Vimeo, where you can find unique and artistic documentary content.\n\n9. **CuriosityStream** - A subscription-based service that offers thousands of documentaries focusing primarily on science, history, technology, and nature.\n\n10. **National Geographic** - Features high-quality short and long-format documentaries focusing on wildlife, environmental issues, and cultural studies.\n\nThese platforms provide access to a variety of documentary styles and subjects, catering to different interests and preferences.",
